{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πέρᾰς</b>, <br /> <i>Epic dialect</i> <b>πεῖραρ</b> (which see), ᾰτος, τό, <b>end, limit, boundary</b>, <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> in local sense, ἐκ περάτων γᾶς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 33.1, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.69; π... αὔλ[ε]ιος θύρα ἐλευθέρα γυναικὶ νενόμιστ᾽ οἰκίας 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 546 \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ π. <b>tip</b>, τοῦ αἰδοίου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 773a21 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; [τῆς ῥινός] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 18(2).28\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; τισὶ τὰ π. ἀλγέει the <b>extremities</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “περὶ αἰτιῶν καὶ σημείων χρονίων παθῶν” 1.7. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2>generally, <b>limit</b>, either opposed to ἀρχή, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Physica” 264b27 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], or including it, τελευτή γε καὶ ἀρχὴ π. ἑκάστου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Parmenides” 137d, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 777b29, “Metaphorical” 1022a4; οὐκ ἔχων π. κακῶν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 1216, compare “Or.” 511, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 632, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 12.88, etc.; π. ἅπασιν ἀνθρώποις ἐστὶ τοῦ βίου θάνατος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.97, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1115a26; εἰ π. μηδὲν ἔσται σφίσι τοῦ ἀπαλλαγῆναι τοῦ κινδύνου 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.42 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἔχειν, ={περαίνεσθαι}, <b>come to an end</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 4.5, 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 60, etc.; π. λαμβάνειν 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.31.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπιθεῖναι τῇ γενέσει π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 776a4; ἐν π. εἶναι 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 5.18.2. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>perfection</b> of a thing, τὸ π. τῆς μαγειρικῆς.. εὑρηκέναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Hegesippus Comicus 1.4, compare 10, 3rd c.BC: Posidippus Comicus 26.17. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> Philos., τὸ τῶν ἀγαθῶν π., τὰ π. τῆς ἡδονῆς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 3p.65U., “Sent.” 20; ἐν τῷ κατὰ φύσιν π. κατακέκλειται τἀγαθόν 4th c.AD: Metrodorus Epigrammaticus “Herc.” 831.8. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>end, object</b>, εὐχῆς, ἐλπίδος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Harm.” 2f \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> Philos., <b>that which limits</b> or <b>has limits</b>, opposed to τὸ ἄπειρον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Pythagoras Philosophus cited in 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 986a23, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 30a, etc.; τὰ ἐλάχιστα καὶ ἀμιγῆ π. [τῆς ἀτόμου] 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 1p.17U.: Comedy texts, of a person, τὸν καλούμενον Π. Philostephanus Comicus 1.3. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>final decision</b>, [οἱ] τὸ π. ἔχοντες τῶν ἐν τῇ πόλει ἁπάντων δικαίων the supreme court, from which there is no appeal, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Dinarchus Orator 3.16. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> πέρας as <i>adverb</i>, <b>at length, at last</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.61, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 2.55.6, etc.; πέρας δ᾽ οὖν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 56.10 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 9.17, 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 261.13 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but also, τὸ π. 'to cut a long story short', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Ἐπιτρέποντες” 70, 316, 470 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]. [In <i>Aeolic dialect</i> the first syllable is short in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 33, long in 84.] \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4009","accentedUnicode":"πέρας","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4008","matchingForm":"πέραν","stepTransliteration":"peran","gloss":"other side","_zh_tw_Gloss":"外, 那邊","_es_Gloss":"otro lado","_zh_Gloss":"外, 那边"}],"shortDef":"end, limit","mediumDef":"<b>an extremity, end, limit</b> <ref='Mat.12.42'>Mt. 12:42</ref>; <ref='Luk.11.31'>Lk. 11:31</ref>; <ref='Rom.10.18'>Rom. 10:18;</ref> <b>an end, conclusion, termination,</b> <ref='Heb.6.16'>Heb. 6:16</ref>*","stepGloss":"end","stepTransliteration":"peras","count":4,"_es_Definition":"extremidad, fin, límite (de la tierra) ; fin, conclusión (HEB.6:16)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) (空間的)極限, 邊界, 盡頭<br>2) (過程的)結束, 終結","_zh_Definition":"1) (空间的)极限, 边界, 尽头<br>2) (过程的)结束, 终结","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"ranh giới; nơi tận cùng. Xem G4008","_zh_tw_Gloss":"極","_es_Gloss":"fin","_zh_Gloss":"极"}]}